Security Countermeasures
Understanding these attacks helps implement proper defenses:

Secure Session Generation:

Use cryptographically secure random number generators
Ensure sufficient entropy (minimum 128 bits)
Implement session rotation after authentication
Session Protection:

Use HTTPS only for session cookies
Implement proper session timeout
Bind sessions to IP addresses when appropriate
Use secure cookie flags (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)
Monitoring and Detection:

Log session creation and usage patterns
Detect unusual session access patterns
Implement session concurrency limits
